#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:1
msgid "pyemscripten_2025_0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:3
msgid ""
"By default, all builds of the Pyodide runtime with Python 3.13 will use the "
"`pyemscripten_2025_0` platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:7
msgid "Prior to {pep}`783`, the platform was referenced as `pyodide_2025_0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:10
msgid "Platform Specification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:12
msgid "CPython and Emscripten Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:14
msgid "**CPython**: 3.13"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:15
msgid "**Emscripten**: 4.0.9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:17
msgid "Unwinding ABIs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:19
msgid ""
"C++ libraries are built with WebAssembly exception handling (`-fwasm-"
"exceptions`) and WebAssembly-based `setjmp`/`longjmp` (`-"
"sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=wasm`). To enable exceptions and `setjmp`/`longjmp`, `-"
"fwasm-exceptions` must be passed at compile time and link time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:24
msgid ""
"The flag `-Z emscripten-wasm-eh` must be passed to Rust. It is necessary to "
"use a Rust nightly after January 15th, 2025, when the `-Z emscripten-wasm-"
"eh` flag was added. All `-Z` flags are gated nightly-only. The `-Z "
"emscripten-wasm-eh` flag will never be stabilized but eventually it will "
"switch to being on by default and then be removed. See [the Rust Major "
"Change Proposal](https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/801) for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:34
msgid "The Rust sysroot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:36
msgid ""
"Rust ships with an Emscripten sysroot built without the `-Z emscripten-wasm-"
"eh` flag so using the standard sysroot will lead to linker errors due to "
"mismatched unwinding ABIs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:40
msgid "Some crates can be built with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:42
msgid "RUSTFLAGS=-Zemscripten-wasm-eh cargo build -Zbuild-std\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:46
msgid "If the crate uses `panic=abort` it may be possible to build with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:48
msgid ""
"cargo build -Z build-std=std,panic_abort -Z build-std-"
"features=panic_immediate_abort\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:52
msgid ""
"but it won't work with any crates that use `cargo vendor` and there seem to "
"be various bugs. Also, when building a large number of packages `-Zbuild-"
"std` inefficiently rebuilds the standard library for each crate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:56
msgid ""
"If not building with `-Zbuild-std`, it is possible to get a compatible "
"sysroot from [pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot](https://github.com/"
"pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot). This is only distributed for Rust "
"nightly-2025-02-01. To use a different Rust nightly, it is possible to clone "
"the `pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot` repository and follow the "
"instructions in the README to build a compatible sysroot. To install the "
"Emscripten sysroot use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:64
msgid ""
"rustup toolchain install nightly-2025-02-01\n"
"TOOLCHAIN_ROOT=$(rustup run nightly-2025-02-01 rustc --print sysroot)\n"
"RUSTLIB=$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT/lib/rustlib\n"
"wget https://github.com/pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot/releases/"
"download/emcc-4.0.9_nightly-2025-02-01/emcc-4.0.9_nightly-2025-02-01.tar."
"bz2\n"
"tar -xf emcc-4.0.9_nightly-2025-02-01.tar.bz2 --directory=$RUSTLIB\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:72
msgid ""
"Note that this is all necessary _even if_ the crate uses `-Cpanic=abort` "
"because the Rust standard library is not built with `-Cpanic=abort` and so "
"there will be linker errors due to pulling in symbols from the standard "
"library that use the wrong unwinding ABI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:77
msgid "Rust Toolchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:79
msgid ""
"A Rust nightly after January 15th, 2025 is required, in order to use the `-Z "
"emscripten-wasm-eh` flag. The recommended toolchain is nightly-2025-02-01 if "
"using the prebuilt sysroot from [pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot]"
"(https://github.com/pyodide/rust-emscripten-wasm-eh-sysroot)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:84
msgid "Runtime Library Loading Path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:86
msgid ""
"There is full support for `RPATH`. The dynamic loader will only load "
"dependencies that are properly specified on the `RPATH`, just being in `/lib/"
"python3.13/site-packages/wheel_name.libs` is not sufficient."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:90
msgid "Libraries Linked to the Main Binary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:92
msgid "The following libraries are statically linked to the binary:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:94
msgid "`libegl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:95
msgid "`libeventloop.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:96
msgid "`libGL`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:97
msgid "`libhtml5_webgl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:98
msgid "`libhtml5.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:99
msgid "`liblz4`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:100
msgid "`libsdl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:101
msgid "`libwebgl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:102
msgid "`libwebsocket.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:103
msgid "`bzip2`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:104
msgid "`zlib`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:106
msgid ""
"All of these come from Emscripten ports and the versions of these libraries "
"are determined by the version of Emscripten we build with. Any symbols from "
"these static libraries may be used by shared libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:110
msgid "Changes from pyemscripten_2024_0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:112
msgid "Emscripten version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:114
msgid "Emscripten was upgraded from **3.1.58** to **4.0.9**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:116
msgid "WASM_BIGINT is now the default"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:118
msgid ""
"In `pyemscripten_2024_0`, `-sWASM_BIGINT` had to be passed explicitly. Since "
"Emscripten 4.0.0, it is the default. No action is required — explicitly "
"passing the flag still works but is no longer necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:122
msgid ""
"Unwinding ABI changed from JavaScript exceptions to WebAssembly exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:124
msgid ""
"`pyemscripten_2024_0` used JavaScript-based exception handling (`-"
"fexceptions`). `pyemscripten_2025_0` uses WebAssembly exception handling (`-"
"fwasm-exceptions` and `-sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=wasm`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:128
msgid ""
"For Rust, the `-Z emscripten-wasm-eh` flag must now be passed to `rustc`, "
"and a compatible sysroot is required (see [The Rust sysroot](#the-rust-"
"sysroot) above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:132
msgid "RPATH is now fully supported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/313.md:134
msgid ""
"In `pyemscripten_2024_0`, RPATH was not supported and the dynamic loader "
"used a patched heuristic based on `wheel_name.libs`. In "
"`pyemscripten_2025_0`, there is full RPATH support and dependencies must be "
"properly specified on the `RPATH`."
msgstr ""
